hing as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":120,"region":120,"country":129,"address":130,"geo":131},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":132,"lon":133},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":135,"type":136},"12704","inventory",{"_":138,"mainLang":139,"languages":140},"Ancient Greek","grc",[138],{"type":142,"bibl":143},"edition",[144],{"author":145,"date":146,"citedRange":147,"ptr":148,"ref":149,"inscriptionDate":146,"title":150,"citation":151,"uri":152,"year":146},"Pugliese Carratelli","1956","no.56",{"target":149},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/PJDRZH66","Silloge dell' epigrafi acrensi","\u003Cspan>G. Pugliese Carratelli, «Silloge dell’ epigrafi acrensi», in \u003Ci>Akrai\u003C/i>, a c. di L. Bernabó Brea (Catania, 1956), 151–81\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/PJDRZH66",{"type":154,"bibl":155},"discussion",[19],{"editor":157,"principal":159,"contributors":160,"change":180},{"_":158,"ref":104},"Jonathan Prag",{"_":158,"ref":104},[161,164,168,172,176],{"_":158,"xml:id":162,"ref":163},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":165,"xml:id":166,"ref":167},"James Cummings","JCu","http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6686-3728",{"_":169,"xml:id":170,"ref":171},"Simona Stoyanova","SS","https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3914-9569",{"_":173,"xml:id":174,"ref":175},"Valentina Mignosa","VM","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7122-2511",{"_":177,"xml:id":178,"ref":179},"Alessia Coccato","Coccato","https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6641-2820",{"_":181,"when":182,"who":104},"Jonathan Prag revised from autopsy","2026-03-09",{"n":108,"url":109,"height":110,"width":111,"desc":112,"surfaceType":113},[185],{"atLeast":186,"atMost":187},15,19,[189],"Pugliese Carratelli, 1956, Silloge dell' epigrafi acrensi",